#Text=Six dead in campus shooting at Northern Illinois University
#Text=Thursday , February 14 , 2008
#Text=Six people were killed and 16 others injured in a shooting at the Northern Illinois University in DeKalb , Illinois , United States .
#Text=Reports indicate that the shooter emerged from a curtain or a screen at the front of an auditorium in Cole Hall armed with a shotgun and two pistols and began shooting .
#Text=Authorities have tentatively identified the shooter as Stephen Kazmierczak .
#Text=NIU officials said the shooter was enrolled at the university as late as the spring semester of 2007 , and was now a student at the University of Illinois in Urbana-Champaign .
#Text=Many of the victims were taken to local hospitals .
#Text=Kishwaukee Community Hospital reported a total of 18 patients brought to the hospital .
#Text=Of the 18 , only two were admitted .
#Text=Eight of the patients were discharged later in the day , while seven were transferred to other regional hospitals for treatment .
#Text=One victim died at Kishwaukee Hospital , another died after being transferred to St. Anthony 's Hospital in Rockford , while the other four fatalities were confirmed at the scene .
#Text=News about the shooting emerged at 3:20 p.m. CST , when a special campus notice was posted on the university 's website , indicating the presence of a gunman on campus .

#Text=Twenty minutes later , NIU announced the cancellation of all classes for the remainder of the evening , and ten minutes after that announcement , NIU officials confirmed there had been a shooting and that emergency personnel were handling the situation .

#Text=George Gaynor , a student in the lecture hall when the shooting occurred , added that the shooter looked like  a skinny white guy with a stocking cap on . "

column1: #Text=The DeKalb County coroner has released the names of all those killed in the attack .
#Text=In addition to the shooter , those killed included Daniel Parmenter , 20 ; Catalina Garcia , 20 ; Ryanne Mace , 19 ; Julianna Gehant , 32 , and Gayle Dubowski , 20 .
#Text=All were students at NIU .
#Text=Chicago news outlets are also reporting names of four of the surviving victims :
#Text=Joseph Peterson , a graduate assistant and instructor of the course in session at the time of the shooting .
#Text=Patrick Korellias , a student in the class at the time of the shooting .
#Text=J.D. Donohue ' , a student in the class at the time of the shooting .
#Text=Ah-Num Rahman , a student in the class at the time of the shooting .
#Text=Rahman was transferred to Good Samaritan Hospital in Downers Grove with shotgun wounds to both arms and the side of her face .
#Text=The other three remain at Kishwaukee Community Hospital .
#Text=NIU president John Peters released some details about the shooter during a press conference following the shooting .
#Text=Kazmierczak had been a student at NIU but transferred to the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign for the current academic year .
#Text=He was pursuing a graduate degree in sociology , with an emphasis in peace and social justice .
#Text=Kazmierczak won a Dean 's Award for a project in 2006 , and was active in the student government while at NIU .

#Text=Officials at a press conference also indicated that Kazmierczak was taking medication for an unspecified condition , and discontinued use of that medication approximately two weeks prior to the shooting .

#Text=The campus of Northern Illinois University is closed until further notice , and officials have announced the cancellation of all athletic events , home and away , through at least Sunday , February 17 .
